The document reports that President Donald Trump criticized former President Joe Biden as a "decrepit corpse" on May 28, 2025, following his cancer diagnosis. This came a week after Trump praised Biden's recovery from stage 4 prostate cancer. The attack was shared on Truth Social and spread online. Trump also accused Democrats of "stealing the 2020 election" and "hijacking the country" using Biden as a frontman. The article notes that there is no credible evidence of election fraud, and Biden has announced plans to treat his illness. Trump, who turns 79 in June, has blamed the previous administration for his challenges since winning the 2024 election. Biden responded on Memorial Day, honoring those who served and their families. The article also mentions that Trump's actions are part of a broader pattern of personal attacks against his political opponents.